  "body": "\r\n### User Story\r\n\r\nAs a user, I want to send messages so that to be sure that the other side would receive them.\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\n*Type*: Bug\r\n\r\n*Summary*: I've created 2 virtual Android devices and started a 1-1 conversation between them. Then I left the devices for some time and resumed the conversation.\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nI expected to receive the messages sent from each of the accounts when navigating to each of the virtual devices.\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\n\r\nSome of the messages got lost, no matter that the following ones were received successfully.\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n\r\n1. Create 2 virtual devices (I don't have real ones to test with them)\r\n2. Setup a Status account for each of them\r\n3. Make them \"friends\"\r\n4. Start a chat conversation between them\r\n5. Stop it at some point for a while (~ 10 minutes in my case)\r\n5. Resume the conversation\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n\r\n* Status version: 0.9.12b\r\n* Operating System: Android\r\n\r\n![screenshot 4](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/5781465/35351273-149b7286-0149-11e8-8776-1670be97282e.png)\r\n\r\n",
